Code of Conduct
Introduction
Welcome to the Open Source Ecosystem Enablement Framework (OSEEF) community! As contributors and maintainers of this project, we are committed to creating a positive and inclusive environment for everyone involved. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for behaviour within the community, as well as the consequences of unacceptable conduct.

Our Pledge
In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming community, we pledge to:

Be respectful and considerate of differing viewpoints and experiences.

Welcome individuals of all backgrounds, regardless of race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, ability, religion, or other personal characteristics.

Be mindful of our language and avoid offensive or harassing behaviour.

Take responsibility for our actions and their impact on others within the community.

Expected Behaviour
We expect all community members to:

Be respectful and inclusive in discussions and interactions.

Use welcoming and inclusive language.

Be collaborative and supportive of each other.

Exercise empathy and understanding towards fellow community members.

Unacceptable Behaviour
Examples of unacceptable behaviour include, but are not limited to:

Harassment, discrimination, or exclusion based on personal characteristics.

Offensive comments, jokes, or imagery.

Intimidation or threats, whether verbal or written.

Any form of unwelcome attention, including trolling or deliberate disruption of discussions.

Advocating for, or encouraging, any of the above behaviour.

Reporting Guidelines
If you believe someone is violating the Code of Conduct, we encourage you to report it by contacting the [Community Manager or Moderators] at [contact email]. All reports will be kept confidential, and individuals involved will be treated with respect.

Consequences
Unacceptable behaviour will not be tolerated. Anyone engaging in such behaviour may be asked to stop, issue an apology, or be temporarily or permanently removed from the community. The severity and impact of the behaviour will determine the appropriate course of action.

Acknowledgment
By participating in this community, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct. Community leaders will enforce this Code of Conduct fairly and consistently, and all community members are expected to comply.

Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.0, available at Contributor Covenant: .
